&nbsp;&quot;Liutlwileng thoroughly took statements from the witnesses and presented them before court. Her thorough investigation ensured that the father was convicted and then sentenced to life imprisonment on Friday.&quot;&nbsp; Free State Police Provincial Commissioner, Lieutenant General Lebeoana Tsumane, welcomed the sentencing as it came at a time when the South African government was raising awareness through the 16 days of activism campaign against violence against women and children.